  "instructions": [
    "Season veal medallions with salt and black pepper. ",
    "Toss capers in olive oil to coat, then set aside.",
    "Heat a skillet over medium-high heat. ",
    "Sear veal medallions for 1 minute on each side, or until they reach 145°F (63°C). ",
    "Transfer veal to a plate and let rest 2 minutes. ",
    "Add garlic to the skillet and sauté for 1 minute, until fragrant.",
    "Add passion fruit pulp, white wine vinegar, and toasted pine nuts to the skillet, stirring to combine.",
    "Return veal to the skillet and spoon some of the sauce over the top. ",
    "Garnish with chopped parsley and shaved Grana Padano cheese. ",
    "Serve immediately, garnished with a sprinkle of capers and a squeeze of lemon juice. ",
    "Refrigerate any leftover veal and sauce for up to 3 days. ",
    "To serve, slice veal thinly against the grain. ",
    "Place veal on a serving platter and spoon some of the sauce over the top. "
  ],
